<br>
Run3<br>
Int3 (general)<br>
MC3<br>
SCM3<br>
SCF3<br>
SCS1<br>
MB<br>
Imp. Fam<br>
SCFM3<br>
QD1<br>
HD<br>
FoMM2<br>
CoX3 ( yeah just wanted those army of swords )<br>
<br>
My guild is sort of a raiding guild. Our position is SSra stage, getting ready for our attempt with emp. SCS is important for it, but again I play in different timezone from my guild and my chance of getting raid item is very slim. So FT is another problem for me. Allegiant Familiar can help me with this. Since I have invested myself alot in crits, and only FoMM3 is left this is also very tempting to me. Manapool is an issue aswell so completing General Inate Int is another factor. Planar power5 is also very very usefull I guess. So my plan were as follows:<br>
<br>
Allegiant Fam / SCS3 / FoMM3 / Exodus<br>
(need to know which one to get 1st in my condition)<br>
Innate Int (General)<br>
Planar Power x 5<br>
PoP int x 10<br>
Quick Damage x 2 (10% haste helps alot)<br>
ND (HP will become important in the future I guess)<br>
<br>
Advices are very apretiated. Thanks in advance<br>
<br>
Enoah<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=laeyakk>Laeyakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/17/03 2:14 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AA suggestion</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Allegiant Fam<br>
FoMM3<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Allegiant Fam is 2 more mana per tick, or ~4% more xp DPS and ~2% more raid DPS.  It also increases aggro that much.<br>
<br>
FoMM3 is ~5% more raid/group DPS, and ~1% more quad DPS.  Is the consensus still that crits do no extra aggro?<br>
<br>
So, Fam is better when quadding, and FoMM is better otherwise.  FoMM costs more.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>SCS3<br>
(need to know which one to get 1st in my condition)<br>
Quick Damage x 2 (10% haste helps alot)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
What is limiting your damage in raids/groups?<br>
<br>
Do you run OOM during a raid/xp group without getting aggro?<br>
<br>
Do you tend to have mana rotting because of aggro?<br>
<br>
When you need to burn stuff down, what is more of a factor: aggro, or casting time?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Exodus<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
A very good toy.  Buy it if you want the ability to do dangerous things without much danger.  =)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Innate Int (General)<br>
PoP int x 10<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Generally a bad idea.  You can get int from items, while most other effects you get from AA are much harder to get that way.<br>
<br>
This is 10 mana per AA point.  The suck.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Planar Power x 5<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Get these as your gear caps out your int.  Each int is 5 mana at L 65, so that's only 25 mana per point of Planar Power.  12.5 mana per AA point isn't a good rate.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
ND (HP will become important in the future I guess)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
12 AA for 10% more hps, that doesn't help pure HP buffs.<br>
<br>
It is nice, but really it is mainly a magelo-inflater, IMO.  =p<br>
