<br>
So I will go for:<br>
<br>
Alleg Fam<br>
SCS3<br>
FOMM3<br>
<br>
For the mean time. This will still require 22 nifty points so it will take a while heh.<br>
<br>
Enoah <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zuratuli>Zuratuli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/19/03 3:50 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AA suggestion</span><hr size=1> Its completely based on you and your guild... If your guild is lacking dps (due to poor gear or just smaller numbers) then fights will last longer and going Oom will happen alot so mana regen is very important when in a guild like this. <br>
<br>
If your guild has high dps (due to lots of members or just flat out good gear) then fights will be much quicker and criticals will be much more important as well as keeping your aggro down.<br>
<br>
Figure out which guild you are in then you can decide. For the first I'd say go Allegiant Familiar first hands down. If you fall in the second category I personally would go for SCS3 then FoMM3. Most likely if in the second category you might peek a bit into low end PoP which is based around the second of these 2 examples. <p><center><img src="http://images.darkenbane.com/image.php/id/1697"><br><b><font face="Comic Sans"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69194">Zuratuli</a> --  I been stompin' in my air force ones for 64 levels.</b></font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=laeyakk>Laeyakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/19/03 5:14 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AA suggestion</span><hr size=1> Bah, I missed your FoMM 2.  =)  My +damage% was from no FoMM to FoMM 3.<br>
<br>
That makes allegent even better compared to it.<br>
<br>
You don't have an aggro problem.  So, go for more DPS first.<br>
<br>
However, when you get all your new spells (I assume you are still gathering them), you might start getting aggro more.  Iceflame and SoS should up your DPS more than those AA, as would a pair of ornate gloves if you can get'm.<br>
